args:
Menoetius's goal was to manipulate Chelsea in
order to get at his younger brother, Prometheus.
Having failed, he shrugs off the party's anger
and leaves the scene. But with the battle won,
the Valentine's dates can finally resume.
This is the power of my...\nNo, of OUR love!
There's only two of them, men! Hold fast!\nCrush them with numbers!
The traitor prince... So much the better!\nWe'll slay them all, here and now!
Seems the imperials have finally given up.\nTalk about clingy. Sheesh!
Tee hee hee! Nope. You kept me safe.
I suppose this might explain a bit\nof why he fraternizes with you lot.
I assume you mean Prometheus.\nBut just what is your aim here?
Merely trying to teach my dear little\nbrother the way of the world.
Humans are sad, fragile garbage—\na fact he was well aware of, once.
But then he started prattling on about\n＂love＂ and ＂bonds＂ like a filthy human...\nPah! You could smell their stink on him.
Love and bonds are hardly foreign\nconcepts to our kind!
Spare me your empty little platitudes.
Love is but a base, feral urge to shape\na partner in the image of your desires.
I was merely trying to point that out—\nand there's nothing like a hands-on\ndemonstration to help a lesson stick.
And you were going to use Chelsea\nto make your bitter little point?!
Or the Flamewyrm there—though I thought\nthis one might drive the matter home\na little bit better than a dragon.
And if a town or two should burn in the\nprocess, so much the better; a salted\nwound lingers overlong in the memory.
You're disgusting. And no matter how you\ntry to hurt your brother, it won't work so\nlong as he has friends to watch over him.
Any wound that you manage to inflict\nwill be healed with the same power of\nlove you just mocked!
It seems I am changing as I forge\nrelationships with people in this castle.
I have changed since meeting you,\n{player_name}. You did this.
Now get lost, 'cause no one wants to\nspend time with a jerk who only knows\nhow to bully his little brother!
And just who do you think you are\nto speak to me so?
I'm a woman in love, scumbag!
And you're about to learn that the price for\ntoying with a woman's heart is heavy!
I'll never forgive you for manipulating\nmy love for Luccy!
Have a hot faceful of a woman's wrath!
Keh heh heh! Don't get so heated, now.\nIt was only a little prank.
I'll come play with you again someday\nif the mood strikes me; you both make\nfor some very amusing toys.
Yeah, I DARE you to show your face again!\n...Ugh. You really chose a grade-A creep\nto get mixed up with today, poor dear.
But I'm fine now, which means I can\nfinally get back to my da—NOOOOOO!
Yeah, I suppose we did spend most\nof the day... Well, fighting.
And we've barely done anything\neven REMOTELY romantic!
We still haven't made it to the accessory\nstore or the dressmakers or the church\nor...or...awww man!
Isn't it a little early to give up?
I know how much you were looking forward\nto today. You really want to end it here?
There's still plenty of time for a date\nif we put some hustle in our bustle.
Luccy, are YOU asking ME on a date?!
YES! YES! A THOUSAND TIMES YES!
I'd say she's made a full recovery.
Looks like it. In that case, should we get\nback to our Valentine's date as well?
*gasp* Darling! Oh, I could just squeeze\nyou to bits right now!
(AAAAAAAAAAH! Luccy asked me out,\nLuccy asked me out, LUCCY ASKED ME!)
(Oh, gosh... I'm so excited...\nI don't even know what to talk about!)
For what you said to him. Menoetius.
I won't allow anyone to threaten Luccy—\nand that includes me!
Yeah, I missed whatever came before it,\nbut I could tell you were fighting for me.
Well, duh! Of course I was!\nYou're REALLY important to me.
You're always thinking of me,\nand it makes me sorta...happy.
(Oh my gosh! He's really not forcing\nhimself just to humor me!)
Close your eyes a sec, Chelsea.
(Come and get it, big guy!\nCome and get EVERYTHING!)
(Our first kiss is basically one step shy\nof proposing! Oh, thank you, Valentine's!)
(Ah! I felt his hand just now!)
This is my Valentine's present\nfrom me to you, Chelsea...
(AAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAH!\nThe world can end now if it wants!\nI love you, I love you, I love you!)
Man, I was gonna give her this necklace,\nbut I think it vapor-locked her brain...
Tee hee... Tee hee hee hee...
(My love might still be a one-way\nstreet right now...)
(But I'll work my hardest to become a\nperson Luccy will choose to love back!)
Tee hee hee... I love you, Luccy!
